The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 6: The Securities and Exchange Board of India today permitted 12-month contracts under the Securities Lending and Borrowing (SLB) framework to make it more attractive. At present, the contract tenure is capped at 30 days. The SLB is a mechanism that was introduced in April 2008 to complement the markets shortselling mechanism.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 6: A high-level review meeting chaired by Prime Minister Manmohan Singh today conceded a suggestion for the immediate sale of a 10 per cent government equity in state-owned telecom giant BSNL.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 6: L.N. Mittal may announce ArcelorMittals Rs 30,000-crore steel project in Karnataka tomorrow after his meeting with the state chief minister B.S. Yeddyurappa.                            
	 London, Jan. 6: Kraft said it had a 1.52 per cent take-up from Cadbury shareholders for its 10.5 billion ($16.8 billion) hostile bid.
                                                                                                                          
